### Phase 4: Developer Ergonomics & Logging

> **Goal:** Clear, actionable error messages. Easy debugging.

---

#### [NEW] [specLogger.ts](file:///Users/durgesh/Desktop/shape-motion-lab/src/specvm/specLogger.ts)

Centralized logging utility:
- `logWarning(context: string, message: string, data?: object)` — yellow warnings
- [logError(context: string, message: string, data?: object)](file:///Users/durgesh/Desktop/shape-motion-lab/scripts/batchRunner.js#41-69) — red errors
- Aggregate warnings per spec (don't spam console with per-frame messages)
- `getSpecReport()` — summary of all issues found during a render

---

#### [MODIFY] [SpecPlayer.tsx](file:///Users/durgesh/Desktop/shape-motion-lab/src/specvm/SpecPlayer.tsx)

Integrate the validation + normalization pipeline:

```typescript
export const SpecPlayer: React.FC<{ spec: MotionSpec }> = ({ spec }) => {
  // Phase 2: validate + normalize once (useMemo)
  const { normalizedSpec, warnings } = useMemo(() => {
    const validation = validateSpec(spec);
    if (validation.warnings.length > 0) {
      validation.warnings.forEach(w => logWarning("Spec", w));
    }
    return { normalizedSpec: normalizeSpec(spec), warnings: validation.warnings };
  }, [spec]);
  
  const frame = useCurrentFrame();
  
  return (
    <AbsoluteFill style={resolveBackground(normalizedSpec.bg)}>
      {normalizedSpec.objects.map(obj => {
        try {
          const state = computeObjectState(frame, normalizedSpec.fps, normalizedSpec, obj);
          return renderObject(obj, state);
        } catch (err) {
          logError("Render", `Object "${obj.id}" failed`, err);
          return null; // Skip broken objects, don't crash
        }
      })}
    </AbsoluteFill>
  );
};
```

